Architecture of Kubernetes:
1. Control Pane = It manages the stae of cluster (group of worker nodes)
 Controller Manager (Manage the state of cluster) - Scheduler (responsible for distributing work across multiple nodes) - etcd (distributed key value pair that holds cluter persistance state)
              API Server (interface and communication medium between Control pane and rest of the cluster)

2. Worker Node = Kubelet + Container Runtime + Pod
  -> Each worker node can have one or more pods
   Pod = It is simple and smallest unit of Kubernetes object model. It can have one or more containers

3. Cluster = Group of worker nodes used to run containerized applications.
 -> All the communication between control pane and worker node done by kubelet.
